{
  "texts": [
    "To this, we responded that the answer lies in implementing industry-wide explicability standards.",
    "One important issue that still requires scholarly attention is non-electoral opinion polling, which involves anything from policy preferences to attitudes towards government and institutions.",
    "You, citizen, are now stimulated in real time with new and updated predictions about other people's views.",
    "Decision-makers also have to face the unprecedented frequency of AI-polling predictions.",
    "What this permanent feedback means for responsiveness, accountability, and for the future of electoral institutions, remains to be seen."
  ]
}